## CRITICAL BUG FOUND: Early-game wipeout
All tournament matches running — new opponents v49, v50 appeared.
Ran local TV12 test → score 0.00! All agents dead by step 100.

### Root cause
`_choose_action()` in semantic_cog.py had early-game survival code:
- Steps 1-20: `hub_camp_heal` — holds (noop) near hub expecting "territory healing +100/tick"
- But territory healing doesn't work at game start (0 junctions, agent not ON hub)
- Agents lose 1 HP/tick, die at step ~50
- Then enter `wipeout_hub_hold` (noop at distance ≤3 from hub) forever
- All agents dead, score 0 for entire game

### Fix
Removed the hub_camp_heal and survival_hold early-game waiting behavior.
Agents now start moving immediately (get gear, mine, explore).
HP jumps to 100 at step 2 from territory healing once agents move.
By step 100: agents have hearts, friendly junctions, actively playing.

### IMPORTANT QUESTION
Was this bug present in the tournament versions we uploaded?
- The AlphaTournamentV7+ classes override `_aligner_action` and `_pressure_budgets`
  but NOT `_choose_action` — so they inherit the base bug from SemanticCogAgentPolicy.
- This means ALL our tournament uploads have this bug!
- v368 (TV12) scored 8.69 despite this bug — either the tournament environment
  has different healing mechanics, or the hub spawns closer to agents.
- If the tournament env heals differently, this fix might not change tournament scores.
- If the tournament env has the same bug, fixing it could massively improve scores.

Running full 5K step test with fix to measure impact.
